name: F-86 Sabre™
description: The F-86 Sabre™ is a United States transonic jet fighter, first deployed during the Korean War. As the first US swept-wing fighter, the F-86 Sabre™ was engineered to counter the Soviet MiG-15. Produced by North American Aviation, the F-86™ was considered one of the most important combat aircraft during the early 1950s.
